<HEADLINE> Rockies 11, Padres 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Todd Hollandsworth hit a grand slam and a solo
home run as the Colorado Rockies beat the San Diego Padres 11-0 on
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Hollandworth's first career grand slam capped a five-run first
inning. He added his 15th homer in the seventh inning to give him a
career-high five RBIs.
</P>
<P>
   Brian Bohanan (10-9) pitched a nine-hit shutout for his second
complete game of the season. The left-hander allowed only three
runners to reach third base, in pitching his second career shutout.
He struck out three and walked three.
</P>
<P>
   Todd Helton went 0-for-4, before being lifted for a pinch-hitter
in the seventh inning, to drop his major league-leading average to
.378.
</P>
<P>
   Adam Eaton (5-3) made his first start since Sept. 3 after
skipping his last turn due to exhaustion. The rookie gave up eight
runs on 11 hits in five innings.
</P>
<P>
   The Rockies opened the first inning with consecutive singles by
Juan Pierre and Nefi Perez. After Eaton retired the next two
batters, Jeffrey Hammonds' infield single loaded the bases.
</P>
<P>
   A passed ball by Wiki Gonzalez allowed Pierre to score, and a
walk to Todd Walker reloaded the bases. Hollandsworth followed with
a drive that just cleared the right-field fence for a 5-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Cirillo and Hammonds reached on singles in the second
before Walker's two-run double.
</P>
<P>
   Brent Mayne, who had three hits, added an RBI single in the
fifth and Cirillo's infield single drove in a run in the seventh.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Hollandsworth has three multihomer games in his career. The
last came when he was playing for Los Angeles on May 11, 1996
against St. Louis. ... Bohanon won his fourth straight road start.
Against the Padres, Bohanon is only 3-7 in 11 career starts. ... In
Eaton's last three starts, he's lasted just 12 innings, allowing 19
earned runs on 24 hits. ... San Diego committed three errors and
has five in the last two games. ... Colorado has scored more runs
(123) in the first inning than any other inning.
</P>
