Wednesday night as the Anaheim Angels rallied from four runs down for an 8-4
victory over the Tampa Bay Devil Rays. Ramon Ortiz (6-5) allowed four runs --
three earned -- and six hits in six-plus innings. He walked three and struck out
six. Cory Lidle was charged with five runs and six hits in 4 1-3 innings, after
allowing only two hits over seven scoreless innings last Friday at Oakland.
</P>
