<HEADLINE> Qatari Plane Hijacked to S. Arabia  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   RIYADH, Saudi Arabia (AP) -- A Qatari Airways plane heading from
Qatar to Jordan was hijacked Thursday to Saudi Arabia, where the
hijacker surrendered to authorities, Saudi officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The plane, en route from the Qatari capital of Doha to the
Jordanian capital of Amman, was surrounded by Saudi authorities
immediately after landing at Hael airport, the officials said.
</P>
