<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Elton John Walks Out on Concert  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LISBON, Portugal (AP) -- Elton John walked out on a sold-out
concert just 30 minutes before it was supposed to start, organizers
said.
</P>
<P>
   The singer appeared worried that the theater at the Estoril
Casino near Lisbon was half-empty, casino spokesman Nuno Lima de
Carvalho said.
</P>
<P>
   ''He said he was going out to get some air, but then he jumped
into his car and went to the airport to catch his private jet. He
never said goodbye or anything to anyone,'' Lima de Carvalho said.
</P>
<P>
   De Carvalho said the audience of 1,250 people, including
government ministers and bank presidents, was slow to move from the
dining room Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   The casino is considering legal action, he said. Tickets for the
show cost more than $200.
</P>
<P>
   Paul Carey, a London spokesman for the singer, said he was
unaware of the incident and had no comment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
