<HEADLINE> Three charged after children found wandering  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   JAMESTOWN, N.Y. (AP) - Two toddlers found wandering naked and
covered with dirt and feces were placed with their grandmother
after their parents - two brothers and a 19-year-old woman - were
jailed.
</P>
<P>
   Henry J. Myers, 31, Ricky L. Myers, 27, and 19-year-old Rhonda
J. Bromley, who police said all lived together with at least three
children in a ''deplorable'' house, were charged with a misdemeanor
count of failing to control a minor after the two boys - 1 and 2 -
were found walking near the house Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Henry Myers is the father of one of the boys, Ricky Myers the
other. Bromley is the mother of both.
</P>
<P>
   Neighbors found the boys wandering in the neighborhood in this
city 58 miles southwest of Buffalo. They cleaned the toddlers up
and went looking for the parents, police said. Neighbors eventually
called police who helped locate the parents.
</P>
<P>
   All three parents said they were asleep and were unaware the
children were missing. Bromley told police an older child, also a
member of the family, must have left the door open on his way to
school. Bromley had been awake but went back to bed because she is
pregnant.
</P>
<P>
   Police said the rooms in the house where the suspects and
children lived were filthy, with clothing strewn about, overfilled
ashtrays and beer cans everywhere and spoiled food on the floor.
The only pieces of furniture were a stereo system, two mattresses
on the floor, a kitchen table and the refrigerator.
</P>
<P>
   The accused were jailed on $1,000 bail and are due in court Nov.
21.
</P>
</TEXT>
