<HEADLINE> Wessels Leads Lancome Trophy Golf  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAINT-NOM LA-BRETECHE, France (AP) -- South African Roger Wessels
fired an 8-under-par 63 Thursday for the first-round lead in the
Lancome Trophy.
</P>
<P>
   Miguel Martin of Spain and Australian Nick O'Hern tied for
second at 64.
</P>
<P>
   Another stroke back were Spaniards Jose Maria Olazabal, the
winner of the 1990 tournament, and Santiago Luna.
</P>
<P>
   Current money leader Darren Clarke from Northern Ireland fired a
67, as did Masters champion Vijay Singh of Fiji.
</P>
<P>
   ''Everything clicked today, '' Wessels said. ''I can't recall
holding a first-day lead in Europe before.''
</P>
<P>
   Wessels had eight birdies, six on the back nine, including four
20-footers.
</P>
</TEXT>
