<HEADLINE> Napa County Eligible for Funds  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- President Clinton declared Napa County a
disaster Thursday, making victims of a Labor Day weekend earthquake
eligible to apply for federal disaster aid.
</P>
<P>
   The magnitude 5.2 earthquake that jolted the heart of California
wine country disrupted utility lines, shattered windows and
storefronts, knocked over chimneys and cracked walls and
foundations. Damage estimates have ranged as high as $50 million.
</P>
<P>
   The Federal Emergency Management Agency will provide grants for
residents and business owners to spend on earthquake-related
expenses. Businesses can also apply for loans from the Small
Business Administration.
</P>
