   NEW YORK (AP) -- Blue chips fell sharply today on profit-taking and concerns
about the drop in the euro currency, but technology stocks moved higher for a
second straight session. The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 94.71 at
11,087.47. On the NYSE, gainers led advancers by a narrow margain. The Nasdaq
composite index rose 19.97 at 3,913.86.
</P>
